{"key":"processedPost-15700919","value":{"id":15700919,"first":15699547,"last":15728596,"when":1327245577,"utime":"01/22/12 05:19 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>EvilMushroom666 said:</b><br /><br />The cost was the main reason I went with a salvaged<br />furnace blower. I have had my hood for over a year now and have had no<br />problems at all with the blower or anything for that matter.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Furnace blowers are far superior to vortex fans.&nbsp; Vortex fans are designed to deliver large amounts of air through a duct for the purpose of supplying or exhausting air.&nbsp; The air from a vortex fan swirls through the duct just as water exits your toilet or smoke exits your chimney.<br /><br />Such is not suitable for a laminar flow hood where you want perfectly straight airflow and static pressure behind the filter, with a very low rate of flow.&nbsp; Order a new furnace blower, or visit your local heat and air shop, and I'd venture a guess to say they have units out back in their bone yard which have been removed from customers homes when a new one was installed, and you could salvage a good blower from one of them cheaply.<br />RR","title":"Re: Will this fan work with Evilmushrooms Flowhood Build?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}